data.title: ordered take out but, had to wait like I ate in.
data.text: I ordered my pizza at 11:30 am got there about 11:15 am. I had to wait for it and i didn't recive it till 11:40 am. I had a chance to sit down and look around this place. it seemed a little tacky if you ask me. The photos on the wall were of pizza, there were many water damage stains on the celing, and the salad bar didn't have any dressing. The lamps were falling apart and in one fixture i seen the wireing (which I am guessing it wasn't a good thing.) The staff seemed to be working and not just standing around doing nothing like most resturants i have been at. The good thing i do give them is that the manager said "sorry for the wait, please take a 2 liter on us." i know other pizza places probably wouldn't do that.

data.title: food and service was wonderful
data.text: I was staying in Omaha and decide to order Valentino's for carry out. I arrived to pickup my food which I had to wait a little bit for them to finish it up which wasn't a big deal. The service was wonderful, all employees were so friendly. My food was made exactly how I ordered it and tasted great. I would definitely recommend this location.

data.title: timely delivery
data.text: I always order delivery from here and everytime they been on time and the pizza was hot. The drivers that I have had come to drop off the food has been very friendly.
